      <title class="- topic/title ">
         <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">12.301</ph> Solicitation provisions
and contract clauses for the acquisition of commercial items.</title>
      <conbody class="- topic/body  concept/conbody ">
         <ol id="d699e13" class="- topic/ol ">
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d726e10" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  In accordance with <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                        format="html"
                        scope="external"
                        class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. 3307</xref>,
contracts for the acquisition of commercial items shall, to the
maximum extent practicable, include only those clauses—</p>
               <ol id="d699e26" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d726e19" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        Required
to implement provisions of law or executive orders applicable to
the acquisition of commercial items; or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d726e24" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        Determined
to be consistent with customary commercial practice.</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d726e29" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  Insert the
following provisions in solicitations for the acquisition of commercial
items, and clauses in solicitations and contracts for the acquisition
of commercial items:</p>
               <ol id="d699e56" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d726e35" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">The provision at <xref href="52.212-1.dita#FAR_52_212_1"
                                 base="i1060447"
                                 outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                 class="- topic/xref ">52.212-1</xref>
                        </i>,<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Instructions
to Offerors-Commercial Items.</i> This provision provides a single,
streamlined set of instructions to be used when soliciting offers
for commercial items and is incorporated in the solicitation by
reference (see Block 27 a, <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">SF 1449</xref>).
The contracting officer may tailor these instructions or provide
additional instructions tailored to the specific acquisition in
accordance with <xref href="12.302.dita#FAR_12_302"
                              base="i1113286"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">12.302</xref>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d726e53" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">The provision
at</i>
                        <xref href="52.212-3.dita#FAR_52_212_3"
                              base="i1060550"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.212-3</xref>, <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Offeror Representations
and Certifications-Commercial Items</i>. This provision provides a
single, consolidated list of representations and certifications
for the acquisition of commercial items and is attached to the solicitation
for offerors to complete. This provision may not be tailored except
in accordance with <xref href="Subpart_1.4.dita#FAR_Subpart_1_4"
                              base="i1126600"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  1.4</xref>. Use
the provision with its Alternate I in solicitations issued by DoD,
NASA, or the Coast Guard.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d726e68" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">The clause
at</i>
                        <xref href="52.212-4.dita#FAR_52_212_4"
                              base="i1060971"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.212-4</xref>, <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Contract
Terms and Conditions-Commercial Items</i>. This clause includes
terms and conditions which are, to the maximum extent practicable,
consistent with customary commercial practices and is incorporated
in the solicitation and contract by reference (see Block 27, <xref href="https://www.gsa.gov/forms-library/solicitationcontractorder-commercial-items"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">SF 1449</xref>).
Use this clause with its Alternate I when a time-and-materials or
labor-hour contract will be awarded. The contracting officer may
tailor this clause in accordance with <xref href="12.302.dita#FAR_12_302"
                              base="i1113286"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">12.302</xref>.</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d726e86" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(4)</ph>
                        <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">The clause
at</i>
                        <xref href="52.212-5.dita#FAR_52_212_5"
                              base="i1061237"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.212-5</xref>, <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Contract
Terms and Conditions Required to Implement Statutes or Executive
Orders-Commercial Items</i>. This clause incorporates by reference
only those clauses required to implement provisions of law or Executive
orders applicable to the acquisition of commercial items.The contracting
officer shall attach this clause to the solicitation and contract
and, using the appropriate clause prescriptions, indicate which,
if any, of the additional clauses cited in <xref href="52.212-5.dita#FAR_52_212_5"
                              base="i1061237"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.212-5</xref>(b) or (c) are
applicable to the specific acquisition. Some of the clauses require
fill-in; the fill-in language should be inserted as directed by <xref href="52.104.dita#FAR_52_104"
                              base="i1064663"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.104</xref>(d). When cost information
is obtained pursuant to <xref href="Part_15.dita#FAR_Part_15"
                              base="i1109360"
                              outputclass="fm:Part"
                              class="- topic/xref ">part  15</xref> to
establish the reasonableness of prices for commercial items, the
contracting officer shall insert the clauses prescribed for this
purpose in an addendum to the solicitation and contract. This clause
may not be tailored.</p>
                     <ol id="d699e155" class="- topic/ol ">
                        <li class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d726e108" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(i)</ph>
                              
                              Use the clause with its Alternate
I when the head of the agency has waived the examination of records
by the Comptroller General in accordance with <xref href="25.1001.dita#FAR_25_1001"
                                    base="i1091029"
                                    outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                                    class="- topic/xref ">25.1001</xref>.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
                           <p id="d726e116" class="- topic/p ">
                              <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(ii)</ph>
                           </p>
                           <ol id="d699e177" class="- topic/ol ">
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d726e121" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(A)</ph>
                                    
                                    If
the acquisition will use funds appropriated or otherwise made available
by the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009 (Pub. L. 111-5),
the contracting officer shall use the clause with its Alternate
II.</p>
                              </li>
                              <li props="Runin" class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d726e126" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(B)</ph>
                                 </p>
                                 <ol id="d699e196" class="- topic/ol ">
                                    <li outputclass="italic" xtrf="12.301_d167e134" class="- topic/li ">
                                       <p id="d726e131" class="- topic/p ">
                                          <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                                          
                                          In the case of a bilateral contract
modification that will use funds appropriated or otherwise made available
by the American Recovery and Reinvestment Act of 2009, the contracting
officer shall specify applicability of Alternate II to that modification.</p>
                                    </li>
                                    <li outputclass="italic" xtrf="12.301_d167e139" class="- topic/li ">
                                       <p id="d726e136" class="- topic/p ">
                                          <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                                          
                                          In the case of a task- or delivery-order
contract in which not all orders will use funds appropriated or
otherwise made available by the American Recovery and Reinvestment
Act of 2009, the contracting officer shall specify the task or delivery
orders to which Alternate II applies.</p>
                                    </li>
                                 </ol>
                              </li>
                              <li class="- topic/li ">
                                 <p id="d726e141" class="- topic/p ">
                                    <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(C)</ph>
                                    
                                    The contracting
officer may not use Alternate I when Alternate II applies.</p>
                              </li>
                           </ol>
                        </li>
                     </ol>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d726e146" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  When the
use of evaluation factors is appropriate, the contracting officer
may—</p>
               <ol id="d699e241" class="- topic/ol ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d726e152" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        Insert the provision at <xref href="52.212-2.dita#FAR_52_212_2"
                              base="i1060530"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">52.212-2</xref>, Evaluation-Commercial
Items, in solicitations for commercial items (see <xref href="12.602.dita#FAR_12_602"
                              base="i1112620"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">12.602</xref>); or</p>
                  </li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">
                     <p id="d726e163" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        Include
a similar provision containing all evaluation factors required by <xref href="13.106.dita#FAR_13_106"
                              base="i1112289"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">13.106</xref>, <xref href="Subpart_14.2.dita#FAR_Subpart_14_2"
                              base="i1110249"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  14.2</xref> or <xref href="Subpart_15.3.dita#FAR_Subpart_15_3"
                              base="i1108536"
                              outputclass="fm:Subpart"
                              class="- topic/xref ">subpart  15.3</xref>, as an
addendum (see <xref href="12.302.dita#FAR_12_302"
                              base="i1113286"
                              outputclass="fm:ParaNumOnly"
                              class="- topic/xref ">12.302</xref>(d)).</p>
                  </li>
               </ol>
            </li>
            <li class="- topic/li ">
               <p id="d726e180" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(d)</ph>
                  
                  Other required
provisions and clauses. Notwithstanding prescriptions contained
elsewhere in the FAR, when acquiring commercial items, contracting
officers shall be required to use only those provisions and clauses
prescribed in this part. The provisions and clauses prescribed in
this part shall be revised, as necessary, to reflect the applicability
of statutes and executive orders to the acquisition of commercial
items.</p>
